  "aiDescription": {
    "summary": "The \"Import NetSuite sales orders\" import is used to add or ignore sales orders in NetSuite. It uses a custom field as the lookup identifier to determine if a sales order already exists. The import is set to be distributed, processed in multiple batches for faster import. It connects to NetSuite using the NetSuite Distributed Adaptor. There are several lookups defined to map values in the import data to their corresponding values in NetSuite. The import has a mapping defined for various fields, including entity, ship address, bill address, custom form, shipping method, and more. It is designed to efficiently import sales orders into NetSuite.",
    "detailed": "This import is named \"Import NetSuite sales orders\" and its purpose is to add or ignore sales orders in NetSuite. The import uses a custom field as the lookup identifier to determine if a sales order already exists in NetSuite. \n\nThe import has a response transform that specifies an expression version. \n\nThe import is set to be distributed, which means it will be processed in multiple batches for faster import. \n\nThere is a preMap hook defined, but it does not contain any code. \n\nThe import is not configured to ignore existing data or missing data. \n\nThe import is not set up to create multiple records from a single parent record. \n\nThe import is configured to connect to NetSuite using the NetSuite Distributed Adaptor. \n\nThe import has several lookups defined. The first lookup is named \"df7de8c447d9441c994dd915b7594d44\" and it is used to map a custom field in the import data to the internal ID of a customer record in NetSuite. \n\nThe second lookup is named \"8742f51ae6c84c96bf2818b20a785d3a\" and it is used to map a shipping method in the import data to a value in NetSuite. \n\nThe third lookup is named \"shipMethodLookup\" and it is used to map different shipping methods in the import data to their corresponding internal IDs in NetSuite. \n\nThe fourth lookup is named \"itemIDLookup\" and it is used to map product IDs in the import data to the internal IDs of item records in NetSuite. \n\nThe import has a mapping defined, which specifies how the fields in the import data should be mapped to the fields in NetSuite. \n\nThe mapping includes fields like entity, custbody_hb_miva_order_id, shipaddr1, shipaddr2, billaddr1, billaddr2, shipcity, shipcountry, shipphone, shipstate, shipzip, shipaddressee, billaddressee, billzip, billstate, billcountry, billphone, billcity, customform, shipattention, trandate, custbody_hb_miva_payment_method, custbody_hb_miva_order_total, salesrep, celigo_recordmode_dynamic, shipmethod, and shippingcost. \n\nThe mapping also includes a list of items, which specifies how the item-related fields in the import data should be mapped to the fields in NetSuite. \n\nOverall, this import is designed to add or ignore sales orders in NetSuite based on a lookup identifier, and it includes mappings for various fields and lookups for mapping specific values in the import data to their corresponding values in NetSuite."
  },
